reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lower Dish Rack fit perfectly, but color was actually gray and not white, as stated
reviews.reviewText: Fair price for a lower rack to replace our 20 year-old one that had developed rust in the past 2 years. Arrived quicker than the estimate, which was fantastic. Advertised as white, but a gray one arrived. I'm not going to return it, but it should be the color advertised. It's odd that the photos of the listing sort of look gray......Hmmm?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Substitute part, fits OK
reviews.reviewText: The part for my original Maytag dishwasher is no longer available. This lower rack with a Whirlpool part number W10139223 is slightly different (lacks a taller-left-hand end with folding shelf), but it fits. The color is more gray than white, doesn't affect the function at all. It comes with the wheels, but you have to change over the sprayer tower in the middle.Price is outrageous, but better than needlessly replacing the whole appliance.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars It do fit my maytag
reviews.reviewText: arrived one day early. One wheel was broke , just used a wheel from the old rack to fix the problem. One other thing the rack is listed as being white its not . I don't know when grey became white. No one but myself knows what is inside my dishwasher, so who cares.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Arrived in great condition. Delivery was better than expected. Excellent price. And didn't have to replace my entire dishwasher. Thank you.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Maytag performance dishwasher model PDB4600AWX replacement rack
reviews.reviewText: This replacement rack fit my Maytag Performance dishwasher model number PDB4600AWX just fine. Actually, it seems sturdier than the original rack, so that is great. My old rack had 6 wheels just like this new one. My silverware basket fits fine in the same place on this new one. It is gray in color as opposed to the original white one, so now my original top rack is white and the new bottom rack is gray which is fine with me. We had no trouble moving the sprayer tower to the new rack, so everything works as expected. I gave 4 stars for the price of $195. 00. That is about one third of a new appliance. I just think it is too much for a dishwasher rack, but I needed to replace my old rusted one, so I ordered it. Also, I noticed yesterday it was $183, but today back up to the price I paid. One final thing, in the description it said, "Hurry, there's only 3 left!" That rushed me into deciding to buy quickly because I didn't want them to sell out and not get one. Well with my purchase, there should be 2 left. One week later it still says 3 left. I guess this tactic worked to get me to buy it quickly for that big price. All in all it works great in my dishwasher.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2014
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Whirlpool-made part for a Maytag dishwasher? Yes.
reviews.reviewText: It seems that Whirlpool makes the part for my Maytag dishwasher. My existing rack was starting to rust, so it had to go, but the dishwasher works great still and similar replacements cost $700 and (way) up. So while this part isn't cheap, it's a far cheaper alternative to replacing the dishwasher. The replacement rack is nearly identical to the existing rack, and an online search quickly pointed me to all the tips I needed to remove the center part from the old rack (which comes separately and costs ~$50) and install it on the new rack. The rack is a perfect fit in my dishwasher. I netted big savings over buying the rack at dealer markup and paying the service tech to "install" it, and even bigger savings over buying a new dishwasher.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Product is functional
reviews.reviewText: The original rack has 4 pairs of wheels and this replacement has only 3 pairs of wheels. When you roll the rack out after washing, it falls in the gap between the side rails on the door and interior body of the dishwasher due to the missing pair of wheels causing a loud crashing sound. When you push the rack back in, it sometimes gets twisted due to the missing set of wheels and jams up.The rack is functional and fits the dishwasher, but the missing pair of wheels is a major design flaw.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 25, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I had no idea that my dishwasher could be quiet again!
reviews.reviewText: Over the years my dishwasher's lower rack had gotten rusted & many prongs broke off & disappeared (where did they go?); it was also a very noisy dishwasher. When I replaced the rack, not only did it fit perfectly, but now that my dishes were being supported properly, there was no more clanging & banging as the cycle ran! My dishwasher is quiet again, AND the dishes are cleaner - again because they are being properly supported in the dishwasher.
